<section class="mt-8 fadeIn">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Research Overview</h2>
  <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
    I investigate the light‑scattering properties of cosmic dust and their impact on the observable universe. By combining computational modelling with polarimetric techniques, I study how tiny dust particles in comets, asteroids, and interstellar clouds influence planetary system formation and the evolution of life on Earth. My work spans:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mt-4">
    <li>Scattering behaviour of dust in comets and asteroids as they approach the Sun.</li>
    <li>Polarisation properties of dust in dark clouds and star clusters.</li>
    <li>Correlation between polarisation maxima/minima and scattering parameters.</li>
    <li>Umov effect studies for silicate, organic, and carbon aggregates.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

